svg.title: scene-fin
svg.text: Semaphores continue to disappear, logs agree but reveal little more.
Log as much semaphore activity as possible
Notice that semaphores disappear consistently on daily cron job runs
Deduce the instigating cron job through elimination (being unable to incite misbehaviour through explicit invocation).
Syslog, Sysdig, Ptrace, stare into the abyss, hope for a signal, wonder if SETI is having better luck.
Spend a long time coming up with, and disproving hypotheses based off of traced events.
With ever thinning hypotheses, take another look at those traced event messages.
Notice an info message, one that innocently declares a logout event, wonder about cleanup.
On this hunch, ask a search engine about Bionic cleaning up semaphores on logout, most importantly; get lucky.
Discover that for Bionic, Systemd (via logind) is configured to remove semaphores on logout by default for user accounts.
Confirm that the account in question lives in user space. Question your sanity, go with this hypothesis anyway on account of scarcity.
Change a logind default or move an account to system space. Entropy flips a table in protest.
